   544	
   545	#### E.5 Atomicity (best-effort regression test) (`test_atomicity.py`)
   546	
   547	```python
   548	@pytest.mark.conformance
   549	def test_task_state_change_visible_only_after_event_appended():
   550	    """spec/v0/04-task-protocol.md §1.3 — every state change MUST be
   551	    accompanied by its event, atomically.
   552	
   553	    NOTE: This is a best-effort regression test, not a certification of
   554	    the §1.3 atomicity invariant. A black-box poll-and-compare cannot
   555	    rule out that the IUT briefly exposed a state without its event in
   556	    a window narrower than the harness can observe; a Jepsen-style
   557	    linearizability check is out of scope for v1.
   558	
   559	    The test drives one transition while concurrently long-poll-
   560	    subscribing to the event log. The assertion is: when the
   561	    long-poll yields the next event, an immediate `GET /tasks/{T}`
   562	    MUST show a state consistent with that event. A subsequent
   563	    follow-up read MUST NOT regress the state. Any window where the
   564	    poll observes a state that the subsequent event does not match
   565	    is a finding.
   566	    """
   567	```
   568	
   569	The wording in the docstring matches what codex review round 0
   570	finding #4 prescribed: "best-effort black-box regression test, not the
   571	conformance proof of atomicity." Chapter 09 §3 explicitly notes that
   572	no v1 scenario certifies §1.3; the v1 suite asserts the testable
   573	consequences.
