   693	#### E.14 Integrate idempotency (`test_integrate_idempotency.py`)
   694	
   695	The fixture model is **simplified** from the pre-review draft per
   696	codex review round 0 finding #8: instead of driving plan → implement →
   697	evaluate to produce a real `success` trial, the test seeds the trial
   698	directly through the storage endpoints in chapter 07 §3-4. The wire
   699	endpoint's normative contract (chapter 07 §5) treats `trial_commit_sha`
   700	as a "well-formed commit SHA" — only the regex shape is checked at the
   701	task-store layer. Reachability is the integrator's MUST (chapter 06
   702	§2), not the task store's. The v1 test uses placeholder 40-hex SHAs.
   703	
   704	| Test | Asserts | Citation |
   705	|---|---|---|
   706	| `test_first_integrate_returns_200_emits_event` | First call with `trial_commit_sha=<40-hex>` returns 200; one `trial.integrated` event appears. | 07 §5 |
   707	| `test_same_value_idempotency` | Second call with the same SHA returns 200; still exactly one `trial.integrated` event. | 07 §5 |
   708	| `test_different_sha_returns_409` | Second call with a different SHA returns 409 `eden://error/invalid-precondition`; stored value unchanged. | 07 §5 |
   709	| `test_integrate_against_non_success_trial_returns_409` | Trial with `status != "success"` rejects integrate with `invalid-precondition`. | 07 §5 |
   710	
   711	The setup helper (`integrate_test_trial_factory`):
   712	
   713	1. `POST /v0/experiments/{E}/proposals` with `state=drafting`,
   714	   `parent_commits=["0"*40]`, `slug="test"`, `priority=0.5`.
   715	2. `POST /v0/experiments/{E}/proposals/{P}/mark-ready`.
   716	3. `POST /v0/experiments/{E}/trials` with `proposal_id=P`,
   717	   `commit_sha="1"*40`, `status=starting`.
   718	4. `POST /v0/experiments/{E}/tasks` for `evaluate` referencing trial.
   719	5. Claim → submit `status=success` with valid metrics → accept.
   720	6. Integrate against the now-`success` trial.
   721	
   722	Steps 1-5 use only chapter-07 endpoints. No git operations, no
   723	worker-host coordination. This keeps 11a + 11b's scope clean of
   724	chapter-03 role semantics.
   725	
   726	### F. Self-validation scenario
   727	
   728	In [`conformance/scenarios/_meta/test_self_validation.py`](../../conformance/scenarios/_meta/test_self_validation.py).
   729	
   730	The pre-review draft's `pytest.main()`-in-pytest design is replaced
   731	with a subprocess pytest invocation per codex review round 0 finding 5.
   732	The meta scenario:
   733	
   734	1. **Constructs a `MisbehavingAdapter`** that wraps `ReferenceAdapter`
   735	   with an in-process httpx-Mocked-Transport-shaped HTTP proxy
   736	   (see below). The proxy:
   737	   - Listens on its own ephemeral port.
   738	   - Forwards all requests transparently to the underlying real IUT.
   739	   - Special-cases ONE URL pattern (`POST /v0/.../tasks/.../submit`
   740	     with a token mismatch detected by reading and re-emitting the
   741	     real backend's response): if the real IUT would have returned
   742	     403 `eden://error/wrong-token`, the proxy mutates the response
   743	     to 200 OK with a fabricated success body.
   744	   - Maintains a `mutation_count` counter incremented whenever it
   745	     mutated a response.
   746	   - Lifecycle is context-managed: enter → start proxy → real IUT;
   747	     exit → real IUT.stop() → proxy.stop().
   748	
   749	2. **Runs three subprocess pytest invocations** via
   750	   `subprocess.run([sys.executable, "-m", "pytest", ...])`:
   751	
   752	   a. **Control run (must pass).** Target:
   753	      `conformance/scenarios/test_claim_tokens.py::test_wrong_token_rejected`
   754	      against the unmodified `ReferenceAdapter`.
   755	      Assertion: exit code 0.
   756	
   757	   b. **Broken run (must fail).** Same target test against
   758	      `MisbehavingAdapter`. Assertion: exit code != 0 AND
   759	      `--json-report-file` shows `test_wrong_token_rejected` as
   760	      `outcome=failed` AND its `longrepr` contains the substring
   761	      `"Expected 403 wrong-token, got 200"` (the exact assertion
   762	      text from the broken scenario; this proves the failure was the
   763	      expected assertion, not an import error or proxy-startup
   764	      error).
   765	
   766	   c. **Hit counter check (must be ≥ 1).** After the broken run,
   767	      read the `MisbehavingAdapter`'s `mutation_count` (exposed via
   768	      a sidecar file the proxy writes to; the meta test reads it
   769	      after the subprocess exits). Assertion: count ≥ 1.
   770	
   771	3. **All three assertions pass** ⇒ the meta scenario is the proof
   772	   that the suite has teeth. Any single-failure fails the meta.
   773	
   774	The proxy implementation lives at
   775	[`conformance/scenarios/_meta/_misbehave_proxy.py`](../../conformance/scenarios/_meta/_misbehave_proxy.py)
   776	and uses `aiohttp` (pinned in `conformance/pyproject.toml`). It is
   777	~80 lines: a single-purpose forwarder that mutates one specific
   778	response shape. It is **not** a general MITM library.
   779	
   780	The misbehaving adapter exposes its own `--shared-token` because the
   781	sidecar misbehaving proxy needs to read+forward authenticated requests
   782	unchanged.
   783	
   784	#### F.1 Why three sub-runs
   785	
   786	- The control run (a) defends against false-positives: if a real bug
   787	  has already broken the wrong-token assertion in the suite, the
   788	  control fails and we know the meta scenario isn't the right
   789	  diagnosis.
   790	- The broken run (b) defends against silent harness regressions: if
   791	  someone refactors the wrong-token check away, the broken run starts
   792	  passing, and the meta fires.
   793	- The hit counter (c) defends against drift in the proxy itself: if
   794	  the harness changes how it tests wrong-token (e.g., starts using a
   795	  different URL or status code), the proxy stops matching the request,
   796	  the broken run still fails (because `wrong-token` no longer fires),
   797	  but the hit counter goes to 0 and the meta fires.
   798	
   799	#### F.2 Why this is not "just an extra test"
   800	
   801	The self-validation scenario is the closest thing to a proof that the
   802	suite asserts what it claims. Chapter 09 §3 leans on this scenario
   803	when it says "every assertion in the suite is keyed off a normative
   804	MUST." The meta is the integrity check that connects the assertion
   805	text to a concrete observable failure.
   806	
   807	### G. Spec chapter 09
   808	
   809	Chapter 09 is short by design. The chapter's job is to declare the
   810	relationship between the spec, the suite, and any IUT — not to
   811	duplicate content from chapters 02 / 04 / 05 / 06 / 07 / 08.
   812	
   813	```markdown
   814	# Conformance
   815	
   816	This chapter declares what conformance to EDEN protocol v0 means and
   817	how it is verified.
   818	
   819	## 1. What conformance is
   820	
   821	A v0-conforming IUT (implementation under test) implements chapter
   822	07's HTTP wire binding with the normative semantics of chapters 02 /
   823	04 / 05 / 06 / 08.
   824	
   825	The v1 conformance suite — under [`conformance/`](../../conformance/)
   826	in this repo — is one expression of that contract: a set of black-box
   827	scenarios that drive an IUT through chapter-07 HTTP and assert
   828	chapter-02/04/05/06/07/08 MUSTs. An IUT that passes the v1 suite is
   829	v0-conformant.
   830	
   831	The suite is one expression, not the only one. A future suite — in a
   832	different language, against a different harness — that drives the same
   833	chapter-07 endpoints and asserts the same MUSTs would be equally
   834	authoritative. The spec is the source of truth; the suite is one
   835	faithful implementation of "what would test that?"
   836	
   837	## 2. The IUT
   838	
   839	An IUT MUST:
   840	
   841	- Expose chapter 07's HTTP binding at a deployment-chosen base URL.
   842	- Accept an experiment configuration whose shape matches
   843	  `experiment-config.schema.json`.
   844	
   845	Anything else — language, deployment topology, persistence, auth
   846	scheme, scaling profile — is a deployment choice. Chapter 07 §11
   847	enumerates further latitude.
   848	
   849	## 3. Assertion vocabulary
   850	
   851	Every assertion in the v1 suite is keyed off a normative MUST in
   852	chapters 02 / 04 / 05 / 06 / 07 / 08. The suite does NOT assert
   853	SHOULDs; SHOULDs are interop guidance, not interop contracts.
   854	
   855	When the spec evolves, the suite evolves with it. A change that
   856	removes a MUST or downgrades it to SHOULD MUST be accompanied by a
   857	matching scenario removal or rewrite.
   858	
   859	The suite intentionally does NOT certify §1.3-class atomicity or §3.2
   860	unforgeability properties; black-box testing cannot prove the absence
   861	of a sufficiently-narrow window or the absence of a sufficiently-weak
   862	random source. The v1 suite asserts the testable consequences of these
   863	invariants (event presence, uniqueness across observed claims) and
   864	labels the regression-style tests as such.
   865	
   866	## 4. Conformance levels
   867	
   868	For v0, there is exactly one conformance level: **v1 conformance** —
   869	passing the v1 suite. The v0 spec defines exactly one wire binding
   870	(chapter 07 HTTP), and the v1 suite drives every IUT through it; the
   871	suite cannot meaningfully separate "core operation semantics" from
   872	"chapter-07 wire shapes" until a second binding exists.
   873	
   874	A future spec lineage that introduces a second wire binding will at
   875	that point split the suite into transport-neutral semantic tests + per-
   876	binding wire tests, and chapter 09 will gain a `core` level claimable
   877	by IUTs implementing only the semantic layer. The marker structure in
   878	[`conformance/`](../../conformance/) anticipates this refactor but does
   879	not enable it in v0.
   880	
   881	## 5. Scenario index (v1)
   882	
   883	| Group | Scope | Spec citations |
   884	|---|---|---|
   885	| Task lifecycle | Every legal/illegal transition. | 04 §1, §3, §4 |
   886	| Claim tokens | Freshness, authorization, no-reclaim-while-claimed. | 04 §3 |
   887	| Submit idempotency | Content-equivalent / divergent / post-terminal. | 04 §4.2, §4.4 |
   888	| Reclamation | Case matrix; token invalidation; trial reconciliation. | 04 §5 |
   889	| Atomicity (regression test) | State + event consistency around a transition. Best-effort, not a certification. | 04 §1.3 |
   890	| Event envelope | Chapter-05 §1 envelope shape; uniqueness. | 05 §1, §1.1 |
   891	| Per-type event payloads | Each registered type's required fields. | 05 §3 |
   892	| Composite commits | Implement-dispatch, implement-terminal, evaluate-terminal cases, implement-reclaim-with-starting-trial. | 05 §2.2 |
   893	| Event delivery | Total order, replay from cursor 0, at-least-once, long-poll subscribe. | 05 §4; 07 §6.2 |
   894	| Status codes | Each operation's spec-pinned status. | 07 §§2-6 |
   895	| Problem+json envelope | Shape + content-type. | 07 §7 |
   896	| Error vocabulary closure | Closed `eden://error/<name>` set; observed exhaustively. | 07 §7 |
   897	| Experiment-id header disagreement | 400 experiment-id-mismatch. | 07 §1.3 |
   898	| Integrate idempotency | Same-value / different-value / preconditions. | 07 §5 |
   899	
   900	v2 (chunk 11c) extends with role-contract scenarios; v3 (chunk 11d)
   901	adds integrator scenarios.
   902	
   903	## 6. Adapter (informative)
   904	
   905	A v1 IUT does NOT need to ship a Python adapter. The reference suite's
   906	adapter shape — under
   907	[`conformance/harness/adapter.py`](../../conformance/harness/adapter.py)
   908	— is one convenience for IUTs that prefer to integrate with the
   909	reference Python harness; it is not a normative requirement. A non-
   910	Python implementor MAY:
   911	
   912	- Write a Python `IutAdapter` subclass that spawns their service.
   913	- Run the suite against an already-running IUT pointed at by an
   914	  environment variable, via a thin Python adapter that simply
   915	  returns an `IutHandle` to that URL.
   916	- Re-implement the suite in another language entirely, asserting the
   917	  same MUSTs.
   918	
   919	The contract between an IUT and a conformance harness is the chapter
   920	07 HTTP binding. Everything else is convenience.
   921	
   922	## 7. Reference posture
   923	
   924	The reference implementation in [`reference/`](../../reference/) is
   925	one demonstration of v0 conformance. CI gates the reference impl on
   926	the v1 suite via the `conformance` job. A reference-impl test failure
   927	that cannot be cited to a normative MUST is either a suite bug or a
   928	spec gap; the resolution is one of: amend the suite, amend the spec,
   929	fix the impl. The reference impl does NOT have authority to
   930	reinterpret the spec.
   931	```
   932	
   933	The chapter is intentionally informative on the adapter shape and on
   934	the v0-reference auth mechanism (chapter 07 §12). Codex review round 0
   935	finding #3 prescribed exactly this: the spec must not require third-
   936	party implementations to expose a Python-harness-friendly lifecycle
   937	shim or a bearer-token auth scheme.
   938	
   939	### H. CI wiring
   940	
   941	New `conformance` job in [`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](../../.github/workflows/ci.yml):
   942	
   943	```yaml
   944	  conformance:
   945	    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
   946	    steps:
   947	      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
   948	      - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v3
   949	      - name: Install workspace
   950	        run: uv sync --all-packages
   951	      - name: Run conformance suite
   952	        run: uv run pytest -q conformance/
   953	      - name: Verify directionality (no reference imports outside adapters)
   954	        run: |
   955	          set -euo pipefail
   956	          if grep -RnE '^(from|import) (reference|eden_)' \
   957	            conformance/harness conformance/scenarios; then
   958	            echo "FAIL: conformance/harness or conformance/scenarios import reference packages."
   959	            exit 1
   960	          fi
   961	      - name: Verify scenario citations
   962	        run: uv run python conformance/tools/check_citations.py
   963	```
   964	
   965	The directionality check makes the layering explicit: `conformance/harness/`
   966	and `conformance/scenarios/` MUST NOT import `reference/` packages.
   967	`conformance/adapters/reference/` is allowed to (that's the layer
   968	where the reference impl is taught how to be a subject).
   969	
   970	The job is **not** added to the branch-protection required-checks set
   971	in this chunk. After 2-3 clean runs on `main`, a follow-up commit can
   972	bump it.
   973	
   974	### I. Spec ↔ harness traceability
   975	
   976	Every test in the suite carries a docstring whose first line cites a
   977	specific spec section, in the format
   978	`spec/v0/<chapter>.md §<sec> — <one-line summary>`. Example:
   979	
