  1006	### J. AGENTS.md update
  1007	
  1008	Add to the Commands table:
  1009	
  1010	| `uv run pytest -q conformance/` | Run the conformance suite against the reference impl. |
  1011	| `uv run pytest -q conformance/ --iut-adapter=<module:Cls>` | Run the conformance suite against a non-reference IUT. |
  1012	| `uv run python conformance/tools/check_citations.py` | Verify every conformance test's docstring cites a real spec section. |
  1013	
  1014	And under "Plan-writing pitfalls", a new entry:
  1015	
  1016	> **Conformance assertions are spec citations, not impl observations.**
  1017	> When adding a scenario, the docstring's first line MUST cite a
  1018	> normative MUST in `spec/v0/<chapter>.md §<sec>`; CI checks the
  1019	> citation resolves AND that the cited section is in the chapter 09
  1020	> §5 scenario index. If the assertion describes behavior the reference
  1021	> impl exhibits but no spec MUST mandates, the choice is to amend the
  1022	> spec (so the assertion is grounded) or drop the assertion (it's an
  1023	> impl-detail observation). Codifying impl observations as conformance
  1024	> assertions silently creates a second source of truth and locks
  1025	> third-party implementations into reference-impl quirks.
  1026	
  1027	### K. Self-host / packaging
  1028	
  1029	The harness is invoked **without** the conformance/ package being a
  1030	development dependency of the reference services — i.e. running
  1031	`uv run pytest -q reference/` doesn't pull in conformance machinery.
  1032	This is enforced by:
  1033	
  1034	- `conformance/pyproject.toml` declares `conformance` as a separate uv
  1035	  workspace member with its own dependency closure (pytest, httpx,
  1036	  aiohttp, pytest-ordering, pytest-json-report).
  1037	- The reference services' tests do NOT import from `conformance/`.
  1038	- Root `pyproject.toml` lists `conformance` under
  1039	  `[tool.uv.workspace] members` but reference packages don't depend
  1040	  on it.
  1041	
  1042	A non-Python implementor can clone the repo, run `uv sync --package
  1043	conformance` (or any equivalent venv), and point pytest at their
  1044	adapter. They never run `uv sync --all-packages`.
  1045	
