**Findings**

1. The revised draft still overclaims what this chunk proves. [plan L57](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:57>) and [plan L821](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:821>) say passing the v1 suite makes an IUT conformant to chapters 02/04/05/06/07/08, but [plan L178](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:178>) and [plan L180](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:180>) still defer role-contract and integrator scenarios to 11c/11d. That means major chapter-06 MUSTs, and a lot of chapter-08 durability/recovery MUSTs, are not in scope yet. Chapter 09 needs to say this is the v1 state-machine/wire subset, not “full v0 conformance.”

2. The plan now claims “all chapter-05 §2.2 composite commits,” but it still misses the actual retry-exhausted `trial.eval_errored` composite. [plan L19](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:19>) and [plan L125](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:125>) make the full-coverage claim; [plan L608](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:608>) expects a `trial.eval_errored` payload test; but [plan L628](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:628>) only tests the non-terminal `status=eval_error` submit path where the trial stays `starting`. The missing scenario is the real `declare_trial_eval_error` terminalization that emits `trial.eval_errored` atomically.

3. The new “every chapter-07 error type is observed at least once” check is not actually satisfiable from the listed scenarios. [plan L135](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:135>) and [plan L672](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:672>) require exhaustive observation of the closed table, but the scenario inventory at [plan L645](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:645>) through [plan L653](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:653>) still has no producer for `eden://error/already-exists`. You need an explicit duplicate-create case, otherwise the closure test either fails or silently stops being exhaustive.

4. `test_at_least_once_via_cursor_replay` is still not testing the thing it cites. [plan L637](</Users/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:637>) uses repeated `GET /events?cursor=0`, which exercises replayability, not `05 §4.3` subscriber delivery semantics. At-least-once in chapter 05 is about active subscribers and reconnect/recovery behavior. If you want a real `§4.3` test, it needs to involve `GET /events/subscribe` and a reconnect / repeated-cursor pattern on that endpoint.

5. The revised adapter story is better, but the Python harness contract is still described more broadly than it actually is. [plan L279](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:279>) through [plan L285](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:285>) and [plan L313](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:313>) say `extra_headers` is enough even for mTLS, but the fixture at [plan L381](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:381>) only passes headers into a plain httpx client. Header-based auth and no auth are covered; mTLS and other transport-level auth are not. Since the adapter is informative this is not a spec blocker, but the plan should stop claiming those schemes fit this interface unless you add a client-factory / httpx-config hook.

**Open Questions / Residual Risks**

1. [plan L639](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:639>) adds a timeout-path subscribe test, but the reference adapter command at [plan L427](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-11-chunk-11a-11b-conformance-harness.md:427>) does not pass a shortened `--subscribe-timeout`. The current default is 30s in the server CLI, so this test will be slow or flaky unless the adapter explicitly lowers it.

2. I treated the chapter-09 language as intended to ship in this chunk. If instead the plan means “chapter 09 will be tightened again in 11d once integrator coverage exists,” that should be said directly, because the current wording reads as a final conformance claim.

**Overall Assessment**

This is materially better than round 0. The marker-boundary problem, the non-citeable HTTP assertions, the auth/adapter overreach, the `pytest.main()` meta-test design, and the direct-role-flow seeding issue are mostly fixed.

The remaining problems are narrower but still important. The biggest one is chapter 09’s current overclaim: as written, it says this chunk certifies full v0 conformance even though 11c/11d are still deferred. Fix that, add the missing `trial.eval_errored` and `already-exists` coverage, and tighten the `§4.3` at-least-once test, and the plan looks ready.
